It is never a good idea to implement a manual wait in a REST API. If it&#39;s a resource you&#39;re waiting for you should poll instead.

But anyways, `System.currentTimeMillis()` will return quite a large number. 
Example: 1426349294842

The request is timing out as the `while` is being iterated over 200 million times given the above logic.

If you really require a wait use `TaskScheduler`

    taskScheduler.schedule(
        () -&gt; {
          // logic to implement after time elapses
        }, 
        new Date(OffsetDateTime.now().plusSeconds(5).toInstant().toEpochMilli())
    );

From http://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-surefire-plugin/examples/skipping-test.html:

    &lt;project&gt;
      [...]
      &lt;build&gt;
        &lt;plugins&gt;
          &lt;plugin&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-surefire-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;2.12.2&lt;/version&gt;
